+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]ntmokey writes "Popular Mechanics has an [1]in-depth look at the
special effects behind the Transformers movie, including some exclusive
shots from Paramount Pictures. Apparently, using real cars as models
presented some interesting problems for the folks at Industrial Light and
Magic, who had to figure out how a recognizable chunk of steel can fold
into robot. In the end, the solution was the development team getting
hands-on in the auto shop. And lots of grease."

