+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Woz on Open Source, DRM                                            |
|   from the when-the-man-talks dept.                                |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Wednesday July 04, @10:32 (Apple)          |
|   http://apple.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/04/144214         |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]destinyland writes "Steve Wozniak just weighed in on DRM, saying "it
doesn't make much sense if these things are going to have DRM forever."
In [1]this great new interview, he complains that even now, only six
songs on his iTunes playlist are DRM-free. He applauds the Open Source
Movement, saying "it's very honorable and it's very good for the
customers." He's even considering publishing the hand-written code for
the Apple II as a manuscript. He's also surprisingly non-commital about
the iPhone. ("Will word of mouth kill it or make it a hit? Who knows?")
He also talks about his favorite pranks, and reveals that "the Secret
Service read me my Miranda rights once.""

Discuss this story at:
    http://apple.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/04/144214

Links:
    0. http://www.destinyland.org/
    1. http://www.10zenmonkeys.com/2007/07/03/steve-wozniak-v-stephen-colbert-and-other-pranks/


