| MPAA Sets Up Fake Site to Catch Pirates                            |
|   from the be-sure-to-include-your-social-security-number dept.    |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday July 04, @19:08 (The Internet)  |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/04/2212213              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

thefickler writes "Media Defender, a company which does the dirty work
for the MPAA, [0]has been caught setting up 'dummy' websites in an
attempt to catch those who download copyrighted videos. The site,
MiiVi.com, complete with a user registration, forum, and "family filter",
offered complete downloads of movies and "fast and easy video downloading
all in one great site." But that's not all; MiiVi also offered client
software to speed up the downloading process. The only catch is, after it
was installed, it searched your computer for other copyrighted files and
reported back."

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/04/2212213

Links:
    0. http://tech.blorge.com/Structure:%20/2007/07/04/mpaas-media-defender-sets-up-fake-site-to-catch-pirates/



